quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"He would say, “Even if I bring you better guidance than what you found your parents following?” They would say, “We reject what you are sent with.”"
  43,25,"So We wreaked vengeance upon them. Behold, then, what was the fate of those who deny"
  43,26,"When Abraham said to his father and his people, “I am innocent of what you worship"
  43,27,"Except for He who created me, for He will guide me.”"
  43,28,"And he made it an enduring word in his progeny, so that they may return"
  43,29,"I gave these and their forefathers some enjoyment, until the truth and a manifest messenger came to them"
  43,30,"But when the truth came to them, they said, “This is sorcery, and we refuse to believe in it.”"
  43,31,"They also said, “If only this Quran was sent down to a man of importance from the two cities.”"
  43,32,"Is it they who allocate the mercy of your Lord? It is We who have allocated their livelihood in this life, and We elevated some of them in rank above others, that some of them would take others in service. But your Lord’s mercy is better than what they amass"
  43,33,"Were it not that humanity would become a single community, We would have provided those who disbelieve in the Most Gracious with roofs of silver to their houses, and stairways by which they ascend"
  43,34,"And doors to their houses, and furnishings on which they recline"
  43,35,"And decorations. Yet all that is nothing but the stuff of this life. Yet the Hereafter, with your Lord, is for the righteous"
  43,36,"Whoever shuns the remembrance of the Most Gracious, We assign for him a devil, to be his companion"
  43,37,"They hinder them from the path, though they think they are guided"
  43,38,"Until, when He comes to Us, he will say, “If only there were between me and you the distance of the two Easts.” What an evil companion"
  43,39,"It will not benefit you on that Day, since you did wrong. You are partners in the suffering"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind, and him who is in evident error"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away, We will wreak vengeance upon them"
  43,42,Or show you what We have promised them; for We have absolute power over them
  43,43,So adhere to what is revealed to you. You are upon a straight path
  43,44,"It is a message for you, and for your people; and you will be questioned"
  43,45,"Ask those of Our messengers We sent before you: “Did We appoint gods besides the Most Gracious to be worshiped?”"
  43,46,"We sent Moses with Our revelations to Pharaoh and his dignitaries. He said, “I am the Messenger of the Lord of the Worlds.”"
  43,47,"But when he showed them Our signs, they started laughing at them"
  43,48,"Each sign We showed them was more marvelous than its counterpart. And We afflicted them with the plagues, so that they may repent"
  43,49,"They said, “O sorcerer, pray to your Lord for us, according to His pledge to you, and then we will be guided.”"
  43,50,"But when We lifted the torment from them, they immediately broke their promise"
  43,51,"Pharaoh proclaimed among his people, saying, “O my people, do I not own the Kingdom of Egypt, and these rivers flow beneath me? Do you not see"
  43,52,"Am I not better than this miserable wretch, who can barely express himself"
  43,53,"Why are bracelets of gold not dropped on him, or they angels came with him in procession?”"
  43,54,"Thus he fooled his people, and they obeyed him. They were wicked people"
  43,55,"And when they provoked Our wrath, We took retribution from them, and We drowned them all"
  43,56,Thus We made them a precedent and an example for the others